(316, 'No option to upload files from different folders at once - New Task', NULL, 4, 82, 15, '<p><strong>No option to upload files from different&nbsp;folders at once-</strong>&nbsp;While submitting a task, In the upload attachments section&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 705)</em>, if we choose one file from our system at first, it gets selected. But when we try to select another file to be uploaded using the same button(&#39;choose files&#39;), the first selected file gets removed and only the second file gets&nbsp;selected.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This needs to be featured with &#39;add another file&#39; button which can be seen in the Upload attachments section of the Learnings and Ideas section from the menu.&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 704)&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><strong>No option to upload files from different&nbsp;folders at once-</strong>&nbsp;While submitting a task, In the upload attachments section&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 705)</em>, if we choose one file from our system at first, it gets selected. But when we try to select another file to be uploaded using the same button(&#39;choose files&#39;), the first selected file gets removed and only the second file gets&nbsp;selected.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This needs to be featured with &#39;add another file&#39; button which can be seen in the Upload attachments section of the Learnings and Ideas section from the menu.&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 704)&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n', '', '<p><strong>No option to upload files from different&nbsp;folders at once-</strong>&nbsp;While submitting a task, In the upload attachments section&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 705)</em>, if we choose one file from our system at first, it gets selected. But when we try to select another file to be uploaded using the same button(&#39;choose files&#39;), the first selected file gets removed and only the second file gets&nbsp;selected.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This needs to be featured with &#39;add another file&#39; button which can be seen in the Upload attachments section of the Learnings and Ideas section from the menu.&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 704)&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n', '', '55', '', 2, 1, '2021-08-10', '2021-08-10', '4', '2021-08-10', 0, 52, '2021-08-10 13:42:47', ''),
