(434, 'Opened Ports', NULL, 3, 67, 12, '<p>To <strong>find a tool</strong> that can provide the details of the Ports that are opened on the servers.&nbsp; We should be able to provide all the server names and it should provide which ports are opened and which ports are closed.</p>\r\n', '<p>To find the open and&nbsp; close ports for the list of servers provided in bulk</p>\r\n', '', '<p>1. Evaluate the tool which can find the open and closed ports for the list of machines provided on the network</p>\r\n', '', '42', '', 2, 2, '2021-11-09', '2021-11-09', '4', '2021-11-09', 0, 56, '2021-11-09 14:31:55', 'Krishnaprasad@digitowork.com'),
(435, 'Eracent Portal', NULL, 8, 85, 20, '<p>To understand the functionality of the Eracent portal and solve use cases around the portal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Eracent has a portal product that helps in submitting the tickets for software, hardware, asset transfer, software unistallation and so on.&nbsp; This portal uses the functionality and data from Eracent, we can use the workflows and alerts from Eracent and build on the portal based on the processes defined for SAM and HAM.</p>\r\n', '', '<p>1. Log into poc.digitowork.com</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. once logged in the URL you willhave the address as poc.digitowork.EnterpriseLM</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Replace EnterpriseLM with portal so the url will be&nbsp;poc.digitowork.portal</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. You will be able to see the various icons on the webpage, if you dont see the icons then you need to go to security settings and give the needed privileges to the user and then the icons will be visible. In all we should have 8 to 10 icons, each icon represents one service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Any help needed please connect with Vinod)</p>\r\n', '', '57', '', 2, 2, '2021-11-11', '2021-11-16', '16', '2021-11-11', 0, 56, '2021-11-11 06:19:39', ''),
(436, 'MFA for TASK management tool', NULL, 3, 47, 12, '<p>To implement multi factor authentication for task management tool</p>\r\n', '<p>Today a user can access task management tool only by user id and login. We also need to implement multi factor authentication for the tool so that user gets the OTP or some other authentication for login</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '<p>1. Identify the best multi factor authentication tool and then integrate the same</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '52,42', '', 2, 2, '2021-11-14', '2021-11-22', '30', '2021-11-14', 0, 56, '2021-11-14 11:52:36', 'srinivasrao@digitowork.com'),
(437, 'Login details of users', NULL, 3, 27, 12, '<p>To record the login and usage details of the users.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Login, Logout date and time and modules visited</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>To keep a track of user activity on the task management tool</p>\r\n', '', '<p>1. User login Logout time along with IP address from where accessed to be recorded</p>\r\n', '', '52,42', '', 2, 2, '2021-11-14', '2021-11-22', '25', '2021-11-14', 0, 56, '2021-11-14 11:55:38', 'srinivasrao@digitowork.com'),
(438, 'Enter not working in multiline text', NULL, 4, 70, 15, '<p>The enter function is not working in multiline text through mobile phone</p>\r\n', '<p>Enter functionality is not working through mobile phone on Task goal, task description and task steps to be executed</p>\r\n', '', '<p>The enter functionality from mobile phone should work in these multi line text area</p>\r\n', '', '55', '', 2, 1, '2021-11-14', '2021-11-15', '2', '2021-11-14', 0, 56, '2021-11-14 12:01:43', 'Krishnaprasad@digitowork.com'),
(439, 'Add forgot password implementation', NULL, 4, 82, 15, '<p>At sign in to portal, add&nbsp;forgot password implementation, in case if someone forgets the password.</p>\r\n', '<p>At sign in to portal, add&nbsp;forgot password implementation, in case if someone forgets the password.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>An email verification can be done.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '<p>At sign in to portal, add&nbsp;forgot password implementation, in case if someone forgets the password.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>An email verification can be done.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Add feature to reset password.</p>\r\n', '', '55', '', 2, 1, '2021-11-17', '2021-11-22', '6', '2021-11-17', 0, 52, '2021-11-17 12:28:44', 'dinesh@digitowork.com,Krishnaprasad@digitowork.com'),
(440, 'Software Request Process thru Portal', NULL, 8, 85, 20, '<p>to design a SW request and approval process thru Portal, workflow and alert</p>\r\n', '<p>1. Software Request</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Approval Process</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. SW Allocation Process</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '<p>1. Select a SW for Deployment</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Requestor requests the SW</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. The request is approved by Manager</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Once approved the SW is allocated to the Employee or Machine</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5.once allocated a mail is sent to user and approved</p>\r\n', '', '57', '', 2, 2, '2021-11-18', '2021-11-22', '8', '2021-11-18', 0, 56, '2021-11-18 16:22:14', ''),
(441, 'Eracent Portal and Workflow Process', NULL, 8, 16, 2, '<p>1. Active / Inactive Catalog<br />\r\n2. Names of Columns to be changed when s/w selection<br />\r\n3. Check Priority of Portal<br />\r\n4. Workflows for s/w req. based on s/w types.<br />\r\n5. Allocation process based on employee<br />\r\n6. S/W Approval.<br />\r\n7. How we can link Portal requests to workflow.<br />\r\n8. If I have 2 same S/W Assets with different statuses then what will be the output in Portal.<br />\r\n9. Can we add UDF I S/W Catalog Approval Req. (Yes / No) If yes then It will go to the manager for approval.<br />\r\n&nbsp;If not It will automatically be approved and allocated.</p>\r\n', '<p>1. Active / Inactive Catalog<br />\r\n2. Names of Columns to be changed when s/w selection<br />\r\n3. Check Priority of Portal<br />\r\n4. Workflows for s/w req. based on s/w types.<br />\r\n5. Allocation process based on employee<br />\r\n6. S/W Approval.<br />\r\n7. How we can link Portal requests to workflow.<br />\r\n8. If I have 2 same S/W Assets with different statuses then what will be the output in Portal.<br />\r\n9. Can we add UDF I S/W Catalog Approval Req. (Yes / No) If yes then It will go to the manager for approval.<br />\r\n&nbsp;If not It will automatically be approved and allocated.</p>\r\n', '', '<p>1. Active / Inactive Catalog<br />\r\n2. Names of Columns to be changed when s/w selection<br />\r\n3. Check Priority of Portal<br />\r\n4. Workflows for s/w req. based on s/w types.<br />\r\n5. Allocation process based on employee<br />\r\n6. S/W Approval.<br />\r\n7. How we can link Portal requests to workflow.<br />\r\n8. If I have 2 same S/W Assets with different statuses then what will be the output in Portal.<br />\r\n9. Can we add UDF I S/W Catalog Approval Req. (Yes / No) If yes then It will go to the manager for approval.<br />\r\n&nbsp;If not It will automatically be approved and allocated.</p>\r\n', '', '57', '', 1, 1, '2021-11-23', '2021-11-23', '8', '2021-11-23', 0, 57, '2021-11-22 18:43:00', 'dinesh@digitowork.com'),
(442, 'CVE 2021-40442', NULL, 3, 83, 12, '<p>The above CVE is an Excel vulnerability, understand the vulnerability and find the patch to plug the vulnerability</p>\r\n', '<p>to plug the Microsoft Remote code execution vulnerability using a patch or any other recommended solution</p>\r\n', '', '<p>1. Understand the vulnerability</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. execute the remediation</p>\r\n', '', '42', '', 2, 2, '2021-11-24', '2021-11-25', '4', '2021-11-24', 0, 56, '2021-11-24 13:07:44', 'Krishnaprasad@digitowork.com'),
(443, 'Asset Returns', NULL, 8, 85, 20, '<p>I bought IT HW assets and I did an asset receipt, after 1 week I want to return the assets. How Will I have the process implemented.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>To have a process for Asset Returns</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '<p>Receive an asset.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then return the asset to the vendor.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '57', '', 2, 2, '2021-11-26', '2021-11-29', '4', '2021-11-26', 0, 56, '2021-11-26 03:55:49', ''),
