(471, 'Catalog Data Vs  Asset Data', NULL, 8, 85, 20, '<p>To reconcile the memory data from catalog to asset data</p>\r\n', '<p>The memory on the HW asset is more or less than the one mentioned on the catalog.</p>\r\n', '', '<p>1. Create catalog with 8mm memory</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Create an asset with same catalog name with memory as 16 MB</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. create a report where the Memory is different in catalog vs asset with the same catalog item name</p>\r\n', '', '57', '', 2, 2, '2022-01-03', '2022-01-04', '4', '2022-01-03', 0, 56, '2022-01-03 13:10:36', ''),
(472, 'Work Order Functionality', NULL, 8, 85, 20, '<p>How does a workorder work for a machine that is given for repair</p>\r\n', '<p>A HW machine is given for repair and how do we track the status of the workorder and then close the same. Once the workorder is closed then it may go to in stock or disposed</p>\r\n', '', '<p>1. HW machine status is moved to Repair</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Workflow is triggered and an email is sent to the technician</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Once the technician updates the workorder status then the asset status changes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '57', '', 2, 2, '2022-01-03', '2022-01-05', '4', '2022-01-03', 0, 56, '2022-01-03 13:22:28', ''),
