(616, 'Green House Gas Calculation', NULL, 8, 85, 20, '<p>To find &amp; calculate the Carbon Foot print of IT Devices.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The IT Devices are:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Laptop</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Desktop</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Network Devices</p>\r\n', '<p>The world is working towards reducing the carbon foot print, the first step in the process is to determine the carbon emission from the various IT devices.&nbsp; The IT Device manufacturing companies provide the Carbon Emission during the lifecyle of&nbsp;a device.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '<p>1. Check for Carbon Emission levels for a different devices from different Manufacturers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Take the Carbon Emission numbers and see how we can bubble up to the whole organziation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Prepare an Enterprise Wide Report for carbon emission or carbon foot print for the IT Devices</p>\r\n', '', '61,42', '', 2, 2, '2022-06-02', '2022-06-02', '8', '2022-06-02', 0, 56, '2022-06-02 08:23:25', ''),
(617, 'Clean up the Catalog Data', NULL, 16, 103, 37, '<p>The goal is to Clean Up the catalog data provided by the UP Team</p>\r\n', '<p>Clean the catalog for the data provided.</p>\r\n', '', '<p>1. Verify the data from the xls sheets</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Add the Findings &amp; Action</p>\r\n', '', '61,57', '', 2, 2, '2022-06-03', '2022-06-06', '8', '2022-06-03', 0, 56, '2022-06-03 10:32:39', ''),
(618, 'Asset in Deployed Status', NULL, 16, 106, 40, '<p>Every asset in Deployed status should have a user assigned to it.&nbsp; If the user is not assigned the record should not get saved</p>\r\n', '<p>The user is mandatory when the Asset Current Status is in Deployed state</p>\r\n', '', '<p>1. Prepare an EPR that will stop saving the record if the user is not assigned and the asset is being saved</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. If the Status of the Asset is other than Deployed then the Asset record should not have a user assigned.&nbsp; If a user is assigned the Asset should not get saved and the validation error should flash.</p>\r\n', '', '61,57', '', 2, 2, '2022-06-08', '2022-06-09', '8', '2022-06-08', 0, 56, '2022-06-08 06:47:57', ''),
(619, 'Types of Fuzzing', NULL, 5, 77, 16, '<p>different types of fuzzing and in which scenario and whch fuzzing type is suitable</p>\r\n', '<p>compariosn of different types of fuzzing</p>\r\n', '', '<p>1. Presentation of types of Fuzzing</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. When to use which type of fuzzing</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Steps for fuzzing</p>\r\n', '', '42', '', 2, 2, '2022-06-09', '2022-06-10', '16', '2022-06-09', 0, 56, '2022-06-09 13:24:23', ''),
(620, 'VAPT-Firewalls', NULL, 5, 77, 16, '<p>Performing VAPT for Firewalls</p>\r\n', '<p>Analyse and document the Technical Approach and Methodolgy for Vulnerability Analysis, Penetration Testing of Firewalls</p>\r\n', '', '<p>List out the steps involved in the&nbsp;Vulnerability Analysis, Penetration Testing of Firewalls</p>\r\n', '', '42', '', 2, 1, '2022-06-13', '2022-06-16', '8', '2022-06-12', 0, 52, '2022-06-12 09:23:04', ''),
(621, 'VAPT-Switches and Routers', NULL, 5, 77, 16, '<p>Performing VAPT for&nbsp;Switches and Routers</p>\r\n', '<p>Analyse and document the Technical Approach and Methodolgy for Vulnerability Analysis, Penetration Testing of Switches and Routers</p>\r\n', '', '<p>List out the steps involved in the&nbsp;Vulnerability Analysis, Penetration Testing of Switches and Routers</p>\r\n', '', '42', '', 2, 2, '2022-06-16', '2022-06-20', '8', '2022-06-12', 0, 52, '2022-06-12 09:26:12', ''),
(622, 'VAPT-  latest windows 10 image', NULL, 5, 77, 16, '<p>Perform VAPT for&nbsp;latest windows 10 image</p>\r\n', '<p>Analyse and document the Technical Approach and Methodolgy for Vulnerability Analysis, Penetration Testing of latest windows 10 image</p>\r\n', '', '<p>List out the steps involved in the Vulnerability Analysis, Penetration Testing of latest windows 10 image</p>\r\n', '', '42', '', 2, 1, '2022-06-20', '2022-06-22', '6', '2022-06-12', 0, 52, '2022-06-12 09:29:45', ''),
(623, 'IT Asset Gate Pass', NULL, 8, 85, 20, '<p>The goal is to build a gate pass process for the IT Assets that are moving out and in the Office Premises.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>A gate pass is issued by the physical security team when an IT Asset is provided to an employee and is moving out of the organization.</p>\r\n', '', '<p>1. Get the IT&nbsp;asset data that is entered in the Gate Pass</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Get the Gate Pass in the format that is needed by the customer in this case conduent.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Lets see if we can print the gatepass format with the data.</p>\r\n', '', '61', '', 2, 2, '2022-06-27', '2022-06-29', '8', '2022-06-27', 0, 56, '2022-06-27 04:43:13', ''),
(624, 'Security for Asset Setup', NULL, 5, 77, 16, '<p>What are the Security tools that needed to be added to an IT Asset before deploying.</p>\r\n', '<p>List down a few MUST HAVE security tools that should be added to any of the IT Assets.</p>\r\n', '', '<p>Look at some of these tools:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1.&nbsp; SCEP</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. SCOM</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. LiveNX</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Orion&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '42', '', 2, 2, '2022-06-28', '2022-07-01', '20', '2022-06-28', 0, 56, '2022-06-28 06:44:21', ''),
(625, 'Generate Asset Tags', NULL, 8, 85, 20, '<p>Generation of Asset tags on the fly based on the criteria selected</p>\r\n', '<p>generating asset tag and able to print it.</p>\r\n', '', '<p>1. Generate Bar code Asset tags on the fly based on the Serial Numbers on Asset Tags or any other data that is loaded</p>\r\n', '', '', '', 2, 2, '2022-07-04', '2022-07-04', '16', '2022-07-04', 2, 56, '2022-07-04 08:17:58', ''),
(626, 'Vamshi Test Task', NULL, 3, 67, 12, '<p>Goal of Task: Download a SQL database&nbsp;from website</p>\r\n', '<p>Task related description:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Example - download a SQL database</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '<p>You can copy complete website with database only with internal website backup, when you have access to the site&rsquo;s contents, e.g. via an FTP protocol.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Website backup includes the two steps: 1At first, make a backup copy of the entire site with all its content, graphics and other data.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can do it just by copying files from a corresponding web server via FTP. 2Secondly, create a database backup to your hard drive.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here, simply copying database component files is not enough; to perform it, you need special database backup software (for example, Handy Backup).</p>\r\n', '', '', '625', 2, 1, '2022-07-06', '2022-07-08', '8', '2022-07-04', 0, 52, '2022-07-04 12:04:58', 'vamshik@digitowork.com,dinesh@digitowork.com,Krishnaprasad@digitowork.com');
