(45, 0, 52, 'Blue Team Cheat sheets Complied', '', 3, '<p><strong>Blue Teams &ndash; Cyber Security Defenders</strong><br />\r\nBlue teams are the defenders. This team almost always works as employees of the company that is undergoing the testing, and are usually members of the IT Security or Data Security divisions of the company&rsquo;s IT group.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Red Teams &ndash; Cyber Security Attackers</strong><br />\r\nRed Teams are the attackers. While not strictly required, Red Teams are usually outside contractors &ndash; since the best testing is done by a team with a lot of knowledge of how to break in, but no knowledge of what security is already in place.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Purple Team &ndash; Cyber Security Attackers and Defenders Combined</strong><br />\r\nPurple Teams are (as their name would suggest) a single group of people who do both Red and Blue testing and securing of a company.Purple Team may be an IT security consulting group brought in for an audit, or employees of the company directly, but they do not focus exclusively on attacking or defending &ndash; they do both.</p>\r\n', '2021-04-20 12:48:27', NULL, NULL, 0, 0),
