(60, 53, 42, '<p>????Note: Please find the attached Screenshots of the below-executed tasks.</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:1092px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; height:38px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:63px\"><strong>SERIAL NO.</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:241px\"><strong>TASK LIST</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap; width:118px\"><strong>STATUS</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap; width:671px\"><strong>COMMENT</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:19px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; white-space:normal; width:63px\">1</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:241px\">Download a virtualization software</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">Completed</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; text-align:left; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">Version - VMware Workstation 16.1.1 Player</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:19px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; white-space:normal; width:63px\">2</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:241px\">Download a ubuntu iso file</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">Completed</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; text-align:left; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">Version - 20.04 LTS</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:19px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; white-space:normal; width:63px\">3</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:241px\">Download a windows 10 iso file</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">Completed</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; text-align:left; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">Version - Windows 10</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:461px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; white-space:normal; width:63px\">4</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:241px\">What is hyper-v, virtual box, vmware workstation</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">Completed</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; text-align:left; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:671px\"><strong>Hypervisor:</strong> Hypervisor is special software that allows you to run one or multiple virtual machines with their own operating systems (guest operating systems) on a physical computer, which is called a host machine.<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<strong>Hyper-V:</strong><br />\r\n			Hyper-V is also called a bare metal hypervisor, and runs directly on a computer&rsquo;s hardware.<br />\r\n			When a physical computer (a host) starts, a Hyper-V hypervisor takes control from BIOS or UEFI.<br />\r\n			Hyper-V can only be installed on Windows-based systems.<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<strong>Virtual box:</strong><br />\r\n			VirtualBox is sometimes called a hosted hypervisor.It is an application that runs on the Operating system and is already installed on a host.<br />\r\n			When a physical computer starts, the operating system installed on the host loads and takes control. A user starts the hypervisor application (VirtualBox) and then starts the needed virtual machines.<br />\r\n			VirtualBox is a multiplatform product.<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			*Hyper-V is always on if the host is powered on, while the VirtualBox and VMware can be started and closed by a user on demand.<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			<strong>VMware:</strong><br />\r\n			A VMware hypervisor runs on an existing host operating system as an application.<br />\r\n			This type provides virtualization services by coordinating calls for CPU, memory, disk, and other I/O (input/output) resources through the host OS.<br />\r\n			For years, VMware has been the leader in virtualization software.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:38px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; white-space:normal; width:63px\">5</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:241px\">Create a separate network in the virtualization software</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">Completed</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; text-align:left; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">NAT (Network Address Translation) Network in Vmware environment player</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:130px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; white-space:normal; width:63px\">6</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:241px\">Understand what is a sandbox environment</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">Completed</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; text-align:left; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:671px\">Sandboxing technology uses virtual servers to test software in an isolated environment.<br />\r\n			Developers can test specific features without worrying about compatibility issues caused by other programs running in the background.<br />\r\n			Sandbox is a copy of your production organization.<br />\r\n			You can create multiple copies of your organization in separate environments for different purposes<br />\r\n			such as development, tesing and training, without compromising the data and applications in your production.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:38px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; white-space:normal; width:63px\">7</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:241px\">Install windows 10 in the virtualization software</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">Completed</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; text-align:left; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:38px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; white-space:normal; width:63px\">8</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:241px\">Check the system specifications after the installation</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">Completed</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; text-align:left; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">cmd command in virtual machine: systeminfo</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:19px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; white-space:normal; width:63px\">9</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:241px\">Make a copy of the virtual machine</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">Completed</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; text-align:left; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:38px; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; white-space:normal; width:63px\">10</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:241px\">Take a snapshot of the virtual Machine after a successful installation</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">Completed</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; text-align:left; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:nowrap\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '<p>At the time of execution of Virtualization tasks(Task No. 5,7,8), my device stopped working&nbsp;and I was unable to make progress in it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then I tried using another Virtualization software(VMware workstation player) and I was able to execute the above-mentioned tasks. But as the free software version&nbsp;features&nbsp;are limited I&nbsp;was unable to execute the last two tasks in it(i.e. 9.Make a copy of the VM and 10.Take a Snapshot of the VM).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Update</strong>(16-04-21): As I couldn&#39;t find an&nbsp;option&nbsp;to take a snapshot and a copy&nbsp;of the VM I implemented in Vmware Workstation Player, I&nbsp;Tried installing VMware Workstation Pro version with 30 days free trial.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In that, while executing the task of Virtualizing Windows 10, I got an error stating- &quot;VMware authorization service is not working&quot; I tried resolving it by repairing the Software from the setup wizard but the problem persists. Please find the&nbsp;attached screenshot named&nbsp;&quot;Screenshot(111)&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Update(17-04-21):&nbsp;VMware free version(VMware workstation player) lacking features of taking Snapshot and Cloning.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>System getting repeatedly hung while running any Virtualization software</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Learned how to perform Virtualization.</li>\r\n	<li>Learned how to download and load an ISO file.</li>\r\n	<li>Learned about different Virtualization techniques and Softwares(Hyper-V, Virtual box, VMware, Sandbox).</li>\r\n	<li>Learned the differences between Cloning and Snapshot.</li>\r\n	<li>Resolving &#39;Authorization service stopped working&#39; error.</li>\r\n	<li>Learned Virtualization in VMware workstation player.</li>\r\n	<li>Learned Virtualization in Oracle Virtual box (Cloning &amp; Snapshot).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-04-15', '2021-04-15', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-04-18 11:19:18', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
