(72, 65, 42, '<p>The cron and at services enable sysadmins to schedule tasks to run at a specific time in the future.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The &#39;at&#39; service specifies a one-time task that runs at a certain time. The &#39;cron&#39; service can schedule tasks on a repetitive basis, such as daily, weekly, or monthly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Cron daemon is a built-in Linux utility that runs processes on your system at a scheduled time. Cron reads the crontab (cron tables) for predefined commands and scripts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The daemon uses a specific syntax to interpret the lines in the crontab configuration tables.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a b c d e /directory/command output</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The parts of a cron command are:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. The first five fields a b c d e specify the time/date and recurrence of the job.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. In the second section, the /directory/command specifies the location and script you want to run.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. The final segment output is optional. It defines how the system notifies the user of the job completion.</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:715px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; height:45px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:106px\"><strong>Field</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:122px\"><strong>Possible Values</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:180px\"><strong>Syntax</strong></td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:305px\"><strong>Description</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:58px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:106px\">[a] &ndash; Minute</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:122px\">0 &ndash; 59</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:180px\">7 * * * *&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:305px\">The cron job is initiated every time the system clock shows 7 in the minute&rsquo;s position.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:78px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:106px\">[b] &ndash; Hour</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:122px\">0 &ndash; 23</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:180px\">0 7 * * *</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:305px\">The cron job runs any time the system clock shows 7am (7pm would be coded as 19).</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:56px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:106px\">[c] &ndash; Day</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:122px\">0 &ndash; 31</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:180px\">0 0 7 * *&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:305px\">The day of the month is 7 which means that the job runs every 7th&nbsp;day of the month.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:65px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:106px\">[d] &ndash; Month</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:122px\">0 = none and 12 = December</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:180px\">0 0 0 7 *</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:305px\">The numerical month is 7 which determines that the job runs only in July.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; height:60px; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:106px\">[e] &ndash; Day of the Week</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:122px\">0 = Sunday and 7 = Sunday</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:180px\">0 0 * * 7&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:bottom; white-space:normal; width:305px\">7 in the current position means that the job would only run on Sundays.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Learned about the cron services in linux</li>\r\n	<li>How to specify and execute cron jobs.</li>\r\n	<li>Cron syntax.</li>\r\n	<li>Uses and Advantages of cron in Linux.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '2021-04-22', '2021-04-22', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-04-22 16:34:17', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(73, 66, 42, '<p>Installed Mysql(Version 8.0.23)&nbsp;in Linux using Terminal commands.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Commands used: sudo apt install mysql-server,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>sudo mysql_secure-installation,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>sudo mysql -u root</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Installed Mysql(Version 8.0.23) in Windows using CMD commands.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Commands used:&nbsp;mysqld --initialize,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>mysqld --console,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>mysql -u root -h localhost -p,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>mysqld --install &quot;MySQL&nbsp; 8.0&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Errors Described as- &quot;Temporary failure resolving &#39;archieve.ubuntu.com&#39; &quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Temporary failure resolving &#39;security.ubuntu.com&#39; &quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<ol>\r\n	<li>How to install MySQL in Ubuntu using Terminal.</li>\r\n	<li>Installing MySQL in Windows 10 using cmd commands.</li>\r\n	<li>How to resolve the Temporary failure errors in Ubuntu Terminal while installing MySQL.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '', '2021-04-23', '2021-04-23', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-04-22 20:02:19', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(74, 67, 42, '<p><strong>(1) </strong>Installed XAMPP Server in Windows 10. (<em>Screenshot- 172</em>)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(2)</strong> In&nbsp;XAMPP Control panel,&nbsp;Apache config-&nbsp;&nbsp;Edited the&nbsp;&quot;httpd.conf&quot; file and changed default ports - &quot;Listen 80&quot;&nbsp; to &quot;Listen 8012&quot;,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;ServerName localhost:80&quot;&nbsp;&nbsp;to &quot;ServerName localhost:8012&quot; (<em>Screenshots- 173,179,180</em>).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(3) </strong>In Apache &quot;httpd-ssl.conf&quot; file changed the default ports- &quot;Listen 443&quot; to &quot;Listen 1443&quot;,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;&lt;VirtualHost _default_:443&gt;&quot; to &quot;&lt;VirtualHost _default_:1443&gt;&quot;,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;ServerName www.example.com:443&quot; to &quot;ServerName www.example.com:1443&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<em>Screenshots- 177,181,182,183</em>).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(4)&nbsp;</strong>Changed Default FTP port to &quot;192&quot;(Any number between 1-65535).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<em>Screenshot- 184</em>).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Installing XAMPP Server.</li>\r\n	<li>Changing default ports in Apache.</li>\r\n	<li>Changing default FTP.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-04-23', '2021-04-23', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-04-23 13:19:44', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(75, 68, 42, '<p>Installed FTP Service as a new user(Visitorg).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(1) Turn windows features on for the Internet Information Services(IIS) through the Control panel. Screenshot- 186.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(2) In Internet Information Services(IIS) Manager, Add a New FTP Site entering FTP site name and physical path of the newly created folder(Named- &#39;ftp&#39;&nbsp;on Desktop).&nbsp;Screenshot- 187, 188</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(3) In the next window, Add the IP address of the current system and select the No SSL option. And in the next window set authentication as basic and allow access to the user account on the current system. Screenshot- 189, 190.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A New FTP Site is created.&nbsp;Screenshot- 191.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(4)Allow FTP Server in the Windows Firewall.&nbsp;Screenshot- 194.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(5) In IIS Add Allow rule in Newly created FTP Site. With User(Newly created windows account) and read &amp; write permissions. Screenshot- 195, 196.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(6) Edit&nbsp;permissions in&nbsp;the &#39;ftp&nbsp;folder(Previously created) and add the New User with full control.&nbsp;Screenshot- 197, 198, 199.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(7) In Command prompt enter into the FTP Service by using the command-</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;ftp 192-168-65-1&quot;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Enter User name and Password and login to the user (Entering the Newly created user credentials).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Execute the &quot;dir&quot; command and the text file present in the ftp folder will be Transferred. Screenshot- 204.</p>\r\n', '<p>FTP Server not working with Browser.</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>How to Setup FTP Server.</li>\r\n	<li>How to access FTP Server using Commands in Command Prompt.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-04-24', '2021-04-24', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-04-24 12:44:55', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(76, 69, 42, '<p>We can Set the permissions from the Internet Information Services(IIS)&nbsp;Manager,&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Steps: Enter into IIS Manager,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Open the FTP Site,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>From FTP Home open the FTP Authorization Rules.&nbsp;<em>Screenshot- 206,</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are two FTP users(in my system):&nbsp;&nbsp;(1)Gursharan Singh, (2)Visitorg</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The 1st user(Gursharan Singh) has Read and Write permissions,</li>\r\n	<li>Whereas 2nd user(Visitorg) has only Read permissions.</li>\r\n	<li><em>Screenshot- 207</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>How to add and&nbsp;remove users in FTP Services.</li>\r\n	<li>How to allow and deny permissions to the Users.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '2021-04-24', '2021-04-24', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-04-24 17:10:25', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(77, 70, 42, '<ul>\r\n	<li>Insalled Apache&nbsp;2.4.46 and Configured the port to 8000. (<em>Screenshot- 209, 217</em>).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(1) Download the zip file of Apache 2.4.46&nbsp;from Apachelounge.com and Extract it to the C-Drive.&nbsp;(<em>Screenshot- 208).</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(2) To install the Apache server, In Command prompt with Administrator privileges and execute the commands- &quot;C:\\Apache24\\bin&quot;, &quot;httpd -k install&quot;.&nbsp;(<em>Screenshot- 209).</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(3) In Services start the Apache 24 service.&nbsp;(<em>Screenshot-210).</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(4) Download and install Microsoft Visual C++ Redistributable. (<em>Screenshot-213).</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(5) To set the port, Open the conf file with notepad from Apache 24 folder previously extracted. Edit the &quot;Listen&quot;&nbsp;and replace the default port with 8000.&nbsp;(<em>Screenshot-217).</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Error: Windows could not start Apache 2.4 on Local Computer.</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>How to install Apache server.</li>\r\n	<li>How to change the default port.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-04-25', '2021-04-25', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-04-25 09:30:53', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(78, 71, 42, '<p>Installed SSH Server and Client and configured the Server&#39;s port to 2200. <em>(Screenshot- 223).</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Steps:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(1) Installing OpenSSH using PowerShell, run PowerShell as an Administrator. Check if the Service is already or partially installed. Execute the command- Get-WindowsCapability -Online | ? Name -like &#39;OpenSSH*&#39;&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 220).</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(2) If the service is not installed or partially installed (Generally client SSH service is pre-installed in Windows 10), Intall the SSH Server using the command-&nbsp;Add-WindowsCapability -Online -Name OpenSSH.Server~~~~0.0.1.0&nbsp;&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 220, 221)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(3)&nbsp;run the command&nbsp;to start the&nbsp;SSHD service- &quot;Start-Service sshd&quot;<small>&nbsp;</small><em>(Screenshot- 222).</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(4) Configure the SSH&nbsp;Server by Executing the following command-</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;New-NetFirewallRule -Name sshd -DisplayName &#39;OpenSSH Server (sshd)&#39; -Enabled True -Direction Inbound -Protocol TCP -Action Allow -LocalPort 2200&quot;&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 223).</em></p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>How to install the SSH Server using powershell</li>\r\n	<li>How to configure the SSH Server to port 2200</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-04-25', '2021-04-25', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-04-25 18:00:12', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(79, 72, 42, '<p>Firewalls can be implemented based on different ways like IP Addresses, Domain Names, Protocols, Programs, Ports, Keywords to allow or deny any access request.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Firewall rules: It&#39;s a Set of criteria that the traffic needs to Match.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Firewall rules in Windows:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(1) Inbound firewall rules define the traffic allowed to the system on which ports and from which sources. If no inbound rules are configured, no incoming traffic is permitted.<br />\r\n(2) Outbound firewall rules define the traffic allowed to leave the system on which ports and to which destinations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Firewall rules in Linux:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(1) Chain Input rules define the trafic allowed to the system from the Internet.<br />\r\n(2) Chain Forward rules are mainly for the Routers, It lets the data pass through by matching the criteria.<br />\r\n(3) Chain Output rules define the traffic allowed to leave the system(Eg: to any website)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We have default policies in Linux which are followed when none of the user-defined criteria is matched.</p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>How Firewall rules work in Windows operating system</li>\r\n	<li>How Firewall rules work in Linux operating system</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '2021-04-20', '2021-04-20', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-04-25 20:49:59', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(80, 73, 42, '<p>Listed all the Open Ports using ss command in Terminal&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 227).</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Commands Used:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Switch user to get root privileges- &#39;sudo su&#39;</li>\r\n	<li>Execute- &#39;sudo ss -tulpn&#39;. This command lists out all the ports(Including closed ports).</li>\r\n	<li>Execute- &#39;sudo ss -tulpn | grep LISTEN&#39;. On execution this command lists out only the ports which are Open.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>Where:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;-t : All TCP ports<br />\r\n-u : All UDP ports<br />\r\n-l : Display listening server sockets<br />\r\n-p : Show the PID and name of the program to which each socket belongs<br />\r\n-n : Don&rsquo;t resolve names<br />\r\n| grep LISTEN : Only display open ports by applying grep command filter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>How to display all the ports in Linux using Commands in Terminal.</li>\r\n	<li>How to display only the open ports(listen).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-04-26', '2021-04-26', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-04-25 21:25:40', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(81, 74, 42, '<p>Firewall rules performed using&nbsp;IP-Tables in Linux Terminal:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>iptables -L</strong>:&nbsp; This command lists out all the Firewall rules present in the System.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>iptables -P FORWARD DROP</strong>: This creates a new rule that makes the Firewall to Deny all&nbsp;the FORWARD default policies.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 228)</em></li>\r\n	<li><strong>iptables -A INPUT -s 192.168.0.23 -j DROP</strong>: This creates a new rule that denies a particular&nbsp;user&nbsp;with IP Address 192.168.0.23 to transfer any data to the system.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 229)</em></li>\r\n	<li><strong>iptables -A INPUT -s 192.168.0.0/24 -p tcp --destination-port 25 -j DROP</strong>: This creates a new rule which denies all the users transferring any data to the system on destination 25(SMTP) with the TCP protocol.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 230)</em></li>\r\n	<li><strong>iptables -D INPUT 2:&nbsp;</strong>This delets a firewall rule at 2nd row&nbsp;present in the Input category(for Incoming data) of IP Table.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 231)</em></li>\r\n	<li><strong>iptables -I INPUT -s 192.168.0.66 -j ACCEPT:&nbsp;</strong>This creates a new rule which adds a specific user to unrestrictedly&nbsp;transfer data to the system.&nbsp; &nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 232).</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>How to implement firewall rules in Linux.</li>\r\n	<li>How to add a new rule to the Firewall rules in Linux system.</li>\r\n	<li>How to delete a particular rule from the Firewall rules.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-04-20', '2021-04-20', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-04-26 10:01:08', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(82, 75, 42, '<ul>\r\n	<li>It&#39;s a System&#39;s feature or sometimes a Router&#39;s feature that Allows the remote control over a PC by receiving the access request from a system connected over the Internet.</li>\r\n	<li>This access request is sent with the port number.</li>\r\n	<li>That port number has to be registered in the Router&#39;s Port Forwarding Application with the destination IP Address in order to allow a person with remote access to the PC.</li>\r\n	<li>Port forwarding is also a way to preserve public IP addresses.</li>\r\n	<li>It can protect servers and clients from unwanted access, &ldquo;hide&rdquo; the services and servers available on a network, and limit access to and from a network.</li>\r\n	<li>Port forwarding is transparent to the end-user and adds an extra layer of security to networks.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>What is Port forwarding.</li>\r\n	<li>How the Port forwarding works.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-04-20', '2021-04-20', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-04-26 10:28:07', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(83, 76, 42, '<p>Acquainted with both the Operating systems Command-Line&nbsp;Interfaces&nbsp;as&nbsp;I&#39;ve been working with the CLIs of Linux and Windows operating systems&nbsp;from the beginning of the Virtualization and Networking tasks.</p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Covered all the basics commands of CLI in Linux and Windows.</li>\r\n	<li>Covered the commands used for Networking as given in the previous tasks.</li>\r\n	<li>Got familiar with the Firewall rules implementation with the previous tasks.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-04-20', '2021-04-20', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-04-26 12:07:18', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(84, 77, 42, '<p>Attached are the Cheatsheets of Linux and Windows operating system Command Line Interface Commands</p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '', '', '2021-04-26', '2021-04-26', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-04-26 13:23:06', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(85, 78, 42, '<ul>\r\n	<li>Port Redirection or Port Forwarding is&nbsp;a System&#39;s feature or sometimes a Router&#39;s feature that Allows the remote control over a PC by receiving the access request from a system connected over the Internet.</li>\r\n	<li>This access request is sent with the port number.</li>\r\n	<li>That port number has to be registered in the Router&#39;s Port Forwarding Application with the destination IP Address in order to allow a person with remote access to the PC.</li>\r\n	<li>Port forwarding is also a way to preserve public IP addresses.</li>\r\n	<li>It can protect servers and clients from unwanted access, &ldquo;hide&rdquo; the services and servers available on a network, and limit access to and from a network.</li>\r\n	<li>Port forwarding is transparent to the end-user and adds an extra layer of security to networks.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>What is Port Redirection</li>\r\n	<li>How the Port Redirection works.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-04-20', '2021-04-20', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-04-26 16:40:31', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
