(128, 116, 42, '<p>Once the Apache server is successfully installed on the system. We can set port by using the following steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(1) Open the Apache24 folder from the C-Drive. <em>(Screenshot- 235)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(2) In the Apache24 folder open the &#39;conf&#39;&nbsp;folder from the list.&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 236)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(3) Open the httpd conf file with the Notepad.&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 237)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(4) In the text file you can find a line as &quot;Listen 80&quot;, Here the default port for the Apache server is 80, We can replace the port number with the&nbsp;required port number.&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 238)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(5) Scrolling down the same httpd file, You can find a line as &quot;ServerName &lt;Name&gt;: 80&quot;, Here you have to set the server name as the local host IP address and the default port 80 with the required port number.&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 239)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(6) Save the file without changing the name or location of the File.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(7) Restart the Apache server using the cmd command, navigating the path to the bin folder of Apache24 folder- &quot;httpd -k restart&quot; and the default server is successfully changed.&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 241, 242)</em></p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>How to Configure and change the default port in Apache server.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-04-27', '2021-04-27', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-04-27 08:52:53', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
