(132, 120, 42, '<p>Successfully installed Kali Linux Operating system using ISO file in Virtualbox.&nbsp; &nbsp; <em>(Screenshot- 435)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(1) In the Tools section of Virtual Box, Click on the &#39;New&#39; button and Enter a name for the OS.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(2) Select the OS Type as &#39;Linux&#39; and as the Kali OS is not listed in the Versions dropdown, Select the &#39;Debian (64 Bit)&#39;. <em>(Screenshot- 430)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(3) When a new Kali VM is created, Go to its settings and in the Storage section load the Downloaded ISO file in &#39;Controller: IDE&#39; by browsing the file in the system.&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 431)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(4) Save the settings and Start the Virtual machine.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(5) Configure the Kali linux OS by step-by-step general process.&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 435)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Installing Kali Linux using ISO file.</li>\r\n	<li>Configuring the Kali Linux OS.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-05-10', '2021-05-11', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-05-10 19:07:10', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N');
