(133, 121, 42, '<p><strong>Nmap:</strong><br />\r\nNmap is an open-source network scanner that is used to recon/scan networks. It is used to discover hosts, ports, and services along with their versions over a network.<br />\r\nIt sends packets to the host and then analyzes the responses in order to produce the desired results. It could even be used for host discovery, operating system detection, or scanning for open ports.<br />\r\nIt is one of the most popular reconnaissance tools. (Screenshot- 434)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Using Nmap:</strong><br />\r\nOpen the terminal and enter the command to get the IP address:<br />\r\n&#39;ifconfig&#39;<br />\r\nOpen the terminal and enter the following command there:<br />\r\n&#39;nmap -sV 34.218.62.116&#39; (IP address)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Burp Suite:</strong><br />\r\nBurp Suite is one of the most popular web application security testing software. It is used as a proxy, so all the requests from the browser with the proxy pass through it.<br />\r\nAnd as the request passes through the burp suite, it allows us to make changes to those requests as per our need which is good for testing vulnerabilities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Using Burp Suite:</strong><br />\r\nOpen the Browser any visit any URL to check the proper working of Browser. (Screenshot- 437)<br />\r\nTo setup burp suite, Open the Browser and in the settings configure the Network settings and change it to Manual. (Screenshot- 438)<br />\r\nOpen terminal and type &ldquo;burpsuite&rdquo; there.<br />\r\nGo to the Proxy tab and turn the interceptor switch to on.<br />\r\nNow visit any URL and it could be seen that the request is captured. (Screenshot- 440)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Wireshark:</strong><br />\r\nWireshark is a network security tool used to analyze or work with data sent over a network. It is used to analyze the packets transmitted over a network.<br />\r\nThese packets may have information like the source IP and the destination IP, the protocol used, the data, and some headers.<br />\r\nThe packets generally have an extension of &ldquo;.pcap&rdquo; which could be read using the Wireshark tool.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Using Wireshark:</strong><br />\r\nOpen the Wireshark application and enter the root password to access it. (Screenshot- 441)<br />\r\nTo trace the packets on the network, Visit any URL (Eg: Youtube.com) from the browser.<br />\r\nNow it can be seen that it display the list of packets along with the headers of these packets (Screenshot- 442)<br />\r\nWe can also search for particular protocol by entering protocol name in the Display filter. (Screenshot- 444, 445)<br />\r\nWe can also search by the website name. Type the following command in the Display filter- &#39;tcp contains youtube&#39; (Screenshot- 446)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Metasploit Framework:</strong><br />\r\nMetasploit is an open-source tool that was designed by Rapid7 technologies. It is one of the world&rsquo;s most used penetration testing frameworks.<br />\r\nIt comes packed with a lot of exploits to exploit the vulnerabilities over a network or operating systems.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Using Metasploit Framework:</strong><br />\r\nEnter the command- &#39;msfconsole&#39; in the Terminal. (Screenshot- 448)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Aircrack-ng:</strong><br />\r\nAircrack is an all in one packet sniffer, WEP and WPA/WPA2 cracker, analyzing tool and a hash capturing tool. It is a tool used for wifi hacking.<br />\r\nIt helps in capturing the package and reading the hashes out of them and even cracking those hashes by various attacks like dictionary attacks. It supports almost all the latest wireless interfaces.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Using Aircrack-ng:</strong><br />\r\nEnter the command- &#39;aircrack-ng&#39; in the Terminal (Screenshot- 449)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Netcat:</strong><br />\r\nNetcat is a networking tool used to work with ports and performing actions like port scanning, port listening, or port redirection.<br />\r\nThis command is even used for Network Debugging or even network daemon testing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Using Netcat:</strong><br />\r\nType &ldquo;nc&rdquo; or &ldquo;netcat&rdquo; in the terminal to use the tool.<br />\r\nTo perform port listening type the following commands in 2 different terminals.<br />\r\n&#39;nc -l -p 1234&#39;<br />\r\n&#39;nc 127.0.0.1 1234&#39;<br />\r\nEnter any message in one of the Terminal and on pressing &#39;Enter&#39; the message is displayed on the another terminal. (Screenshot- 450)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>John the Ripper:</strong><br />\r\nJohn the Ripper is a great tool for cracking passwords using some famous brute for attacks like dictionary attack or custom wordlist attack etc.<br />\r\nIt is even used to crack the hashes or passwords for the zipped or compressed files and even locked files as well. It has many available options to crack hashes or passwords.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Using John the Ripper:</strong><br />\r\nType &ldquo;john&rdquo; in the terminal to use the tool. (Screenshot- 451)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>sqlmap:</strong><br />\r\nsqlmap is one of the best tools to perform SQL injection attacks. It just automates the process of testing a parameter for SQL injection and even automates the process of exploitation of the vulnerable parameter.<br />\r\nIt is a great tool as it detects the database on its own so we just have to provide a URL to check whether the parameter in the URL is vulnerable or not,<br />\r\nwe could even use the requested file to check for POST parameters.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Using sqlmap:</strong><br />\r\nType &#39;sqlmap&#39; in the terminal to use the tool. (Screenshot- 452)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Autopsy:</strong><br />\r\nAutopsy is a digital forensics tool that is used to gather the information form forensics. Or in other words, this tool is used to investigate files or logs to learn about what exactly was done with the system.<br />\r\nIt could even be used as a recovery software to recover files from a memory card or a pen drive.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Using Autopsy:</strong><br />\r\nType &ldquo;autopsy&rdquo; in the terminal to use the tool. (Screenshot- 453)<br />\r\nVisit &#39;http://localhost:9999/autopsy&#39; in order to use the tool.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Social Engineering Toolkit:</strong><br />\r\nSocial Engineering Toolkit is a collection of tools that could be used to perform social engineering attacks. These tools use and manipulate human behavior for information gathering.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Using Social Engineering Toolkit:</strong><br />\r\nType &ldquo;setoolkit&rdquo; in the terminal.<br />\r\nAgree to the terms and conditions to start using the social engineering toolkit. (Screenshot- 454, 455)</p>\r\n', '<p>The system got hung due to the fewer machine memory.</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Learning about different Kali Linux inbuilt tools</li>\r\n	<li>Using the different&nbsp;tools like Nmap, Burp Suite, Wireshark, Metasploit framework, Aircrack-ng , Netcat, John the ripper, sqlmap, Autopsy, Social Engineering toolkit</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-05-12', '2021-05-14', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-05-14 10:19:52', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(134, 122, 42, '<p>Popular tools for brute force attacks:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Aircrack-ng</strong><br />\r\nThis is a popular brute force wifi password cracking tool. This tool comes with WEP/WPA/WPA2-PSK cracker and analysis tools to perform attacks on Wi-Fi.<br />\r\nIt basically performs dictionary attacks against a wireless network to guess the password. The success of the attack depends on the dictionary of passwords. The better and more effective the password dictionary is, the more likely it is that it will crack the password.<br />\r\nIt is available for Windows and Linux platforms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>John the Ripper</strong><br />\r\nThis free password-cracking software was initially developed for Unix systems. Later, developers released it for various other platforms like Linux, Windows, etc.<br />\r\nIt has been the most used tool for performing brute force attacks for a long time.&nbsp;<br />\r\nWe can use this either to identify weak passwords or to crack passwords for breaking authentication.<br />\r\nThis tool is very popular and combines various password-cracking features. It can automatically detect the type of hashing used in a password. Therefore, you can also run it against encrypted password storage.<br />\r\nBasically, it can perform brute force attacks with all possible passwords by combining text and numbers. However, you can also use it with a dictionary of passwords to perform dictionary attacks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Rainbow Crack</strong><br />\r\nRainbow Crack is also a popular brute-forcing tool used for password cracking. It generates rainbow tables for use while performing the attack.<br />\r\nRainbow tables are pre-computed. It helps in reducing the time in performing the attack.<br />\r\nIt is available for both Windows and Linux and supports all the latest versions of these platforms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>L0phtCrack</strong><br />\r\nL0phtCrack is known for its ability to crack Windows passwords. It uses dictionary attacks, brute force attacks, hybrid attacks, and rainbow tables.<br />\r\nThe most notable features of L0phtcrack are scheduling, hash extraction from 64-bit Windows versions, multiprocessor algorithms, and network monitoring and decoding.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Ophcrack</strong><br />\r\nOphcrack is another brute-forcing tool specially used for cracking Windows passwords.<br />\r\nIt cracks Windows passwords by using LM hashes through rainbow tables. It is a free and open-source tool.<br />\r\nIt can crack a Windows password in a few minutes. By default, Ophcrack comes with rainbow tables to crack passwords of less than 14 characters which contain only alphanumeric characters.<br />\r\nOther rainbow tables are also available to download.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Hashcat</strong><br />\r\nHashcat claims to be the fastest CPU-based password cracking tool. It is free and comes for Linux, Windows, and Mac OS platforms.<br />\r\nHashcat supports various hashing algorithms including LM Hashes, MD4, MD5, SHA-family, Unix Crypt formats, MySQL and Cisco PIX.<br />\r\nIt supports various attacks including brute force attacks, combinator attacks, dictionary attacks, fingerprint attacks, hybrid attacks, mask attacks, permutation attacks, rule-based attacks, table-lookup attacks, and toggle-case attacks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Ncrack</strong><br />\r\nNcrack is also a popular password-cracking tool for cracking network authentications. It supports various protocols including SSH, HTTP(S), and Telnet.<br />\r\nIt can perform different attacks including brute-forcing attacks. It supports various platforms including Linux, Windows, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>THC Hydra</strong><br />\r\nTHC Hydra is known for its ability to crack passwords of network authentications by performing brute force attacks.<br />\r\nIt performs dictionary attacks against more than 30 protocols including Telnet, FTP, HTTP, HTTPS, SMB, etc. It is available for various platforms including Linux, Windows.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Shodan.io</strong><br />\r\nSHodan is one of the most popular Search Engines used to find the devices connected to the Internet.<br />\r\nIt finds IoT(Internet of Things), the things which are connected to the internet like Routers, Switches, Webcams, Power plants, etc.<br />\r\nWhereas Google finds the Web pages, Shodan finds the Devices connected over the Public IPs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>To use the Shodan search engine</strong>, Visit the website- &#39;www.shodan.io&#39;<br />\r\nIn the search bar, we can search for all the Webcams from New York City. <em>(Screenshot- 457)</em><br />\r\nWe can also search by Port number, Eg: Port 443 (HTTPS port number). <em>(Screenshot- 458)</em><br />\r\nSearch can also be filtered by Country, by searching the two-letter short form of any Country&#39;s Name. Eg: webcam Country:&quot;CA&quot; (Canada). <em>(Screenshot- 459)</em></p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Overview of various Brute forcing tools like Aircrack-ng, John the Ripper, Rainbow Crack, Hydra, etc.</li>\r\n	<li>Shodan Search Engine overview and working.</li>\r\n	<li>Using Shodan Search engine to find different public devices connected to the Internet all over the Globe.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-05-14', '2021-05-15', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-05-16 03:17:39', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(135, 123, 42, '<p>As the default port for RDP(Remote Desktop Protocol) is 3389, IP addresses of the Systems having Remote connection port open are viewed by searching &#39;port:3389&#39; in the Shodan Search Engine.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>(Screenshot- 461)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: As it was&nbsp;not mentioned in the Task description about which tool I have to use here, I&#39;ve referred to the previous task which was an Introduction to Shodan, and the upcoming task-126 where it&#39;s mentioned to use Shodan for a similar task.</p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Shodan Search Engine working</li>\r\n	<li>Getting Filtered search by Port numbers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-05-17', '2021-05-17', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-05-17 13:53:11', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(136, 124, 42, '<p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(1)</strong> Place both the machines i.e., Kali Linux and the remote machine on the same network (here we are using NAT Network)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(2)</strong> Note the IP Address of the target remote machine (here we are using windows 8) and its IP Address is 10.0.2.15.&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot-&nbsp;703)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(3) </strong>Open the Kali linux terminal and ping the remote machine using the IP Address noted previously.<em> (Screenshot- 702)</em></p>\r\n', '<p>low RAM to run more than one virtual&nbsp;machines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Update: RAM got updated</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Connecting remote machine using its IP Address</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-08-06', '2021-08-08', 1, '4', 'Y', 0, '2021-08-07 20:50:26', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(137, 125, 42, '<p>Successfully accessed the remote machine using RDP. <em>(Screenshot- 700)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(1)</strong> Enable RDP in the remote Windows machine. i.e., Open the control panel from the windows machine, and in the &#39;System&#39; section click on the &#39;Allow remote access&#39;. Enable it and save the settings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(2)</strong> Now from the Ubuntu machine open the Remmina application. Mostly Remmina comes preinstalled in Ubuntu OS.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(3)</strong> In Remmina click on the &#39;New connection profile&#39; present on the top left corner of the window.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(4)</strong> Enter the IP address of the remote windows machine in the &#39;Server section&#39; and also the user credentials of the remote machine through which you wish to log in.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>(Screenshot- 701)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(5)</strong> Now click on the &#39;Save and Connect&#39; button at the bottom of the window.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And the windows machine&#39;s remote access is gained from the present ubuntu machine. <em>(Screenshot- 699, 700)</em></p>\r\n', '', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Establishing remote access connection of windows machine from&nbsp;the Linux based machine.</li>\r\n	<li>Using Remmina- A tool of Ubuntu used to establish connections such as RDP, SSH, etc.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-08-06', '2021-08-08', 1, '4', 'Y', 0, '2021-08-07 20:52:54', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(138, 126, 42, '<p>Got the IP Addresses of the Systems&nbsp;connected to the&nbsp;Cisco Routers. (Screenshot- 464)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We can filter the search for different routers by their names&nbsp;like Netgear.</p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Searching Shodan for the Systems connected to the Particular Routers.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-05-17', '2021-05-17', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-05-17 14:24:45', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(139, 127, 42, '<p>Prerequisite for Installing Shodan on Kali Linux is&nbsp;a pip package installer for Python 3 Since the CLI for shodan is provided alongside the Python Library.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Installing pip for Python 3 using the command in Kali Linux Terminal- &#39;sudo apt install python3-pip&#39; <em>(Screenshot- 476)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>After&nbsp;installing the pip, Install&nbsp;Shodan CLI using the command- &#39;pip install -U -user shodan&#39;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now Initialize Shodal CLI with API key. We can get an API key from the official website of Shodan. <em>(Screenshot- 477)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To Initialize Shodan CLI enter the API key in command as &#39;shodan init &lt;API Key&gt;&#39; <em>(Screenshot- 478)</em></p>\r\n', '<p>&nbsp;-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Installing the CLI for Shodan.</li>\r\n	<li>Initializing Shodan CLI with API key.</li>\r\n	<li>Installing pip for Python 3 in Kali linux.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-05-19', '2021-05-19', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-05-19 02:39:09', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(140, 128, 42, '<p><strong>Options in&nbsp;Shodan:</strong> After successfully installing the CLI for Shodan and initializing it with API key, we can List out the options for shodan. Run the Command- &#39;shodan&#39; in the Terminal. <em>(Screenshot- 479)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Exploring shodan using Terminal:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(1)&nbsp;To get the count of our search results</strong>, Run the command- &#39;shodan count webcam&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>(Screenshot- 480)</em>&nbsp;It displays the total count of open Webams all over the globe using shodan search.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(2)&nbsp;To get the details of any host</strong>, Run the command- &#39;shodan host 189.201.128.250&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>(Screenshot- 481)</em> It displays all the details like Hostname, Location, Open ports&nbsp;of the host machine with IP address 189.201.128.250&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(3) To get the Internet-facing IP</strong> of the current system, Run the command- &#39;shodan myip&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>(Screenshot- 482)</em> This displays the IP address which is used by the Internet service provider(ISP).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(4)&nbsp;To Download the search data</strong>, Run the command-</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&#39;shodan download webcam-data webcam&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>(Screenshot- 483)</em> This downloads all the data of the webcams from shodan search. Here webcam-data is the JSON file name in which the search data will be saved.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(5)&nbsp;To view the data downloaded previously</strong> using the &#39;download&#39; command from the &#39;webcam-data&#39; file, Run the command- &#39;shodan parse --fields ip_str,port --separator , webcam-data.json.gz&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>(Screenshot- 484)</em> Here we filtered the search by IP address and Port from the &#39;webcam-data.json&#39; file.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(6) To perform a detailed search,&nbsp;</strong>Run the command- &#39;shodan search --fields ip_str,port webcams&#39;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>(Screenshot- 485, 486)</em> This displays IP addresses and the Ports used by the open Webcams all over the globe&nbsp;from&nbsp;shodan search.</p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Viewing options in Shodan CLI</li>\r\n	<li>Getting the count of Search results from shodan search</li>\r\n	<li>Downloading the searched data</li>\r\n	<li>Viewing the downloaded search data by applying filters saved in the created JSON file</li>\r\n	<li>Getting IP address used by the ISP</li>\r\n	<li>Performing a detailed search for the Internet of Things</li>\r\n	<li>Getting host details</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-05-19', '2021-05-19', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-05-19 10:53:17', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
