(148, 136, 42, '<p>Installed Ubuntu Server 20.04.2 LTS</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Steps to do so:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(1)</strong> Download the ISO file for Ubuntu Server 20.04.2 from Ubuntu.com</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(2)</strong> Setup a&nbsp;New Virtual machine for Ubuntu Server in the Virtual box (including loading of ISO file)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(3)&nbsp;</strong>Start the Virtual machine and the Installation setup of Ubuntu will be loaded. Select the language and keyboard type. (Screenshot- 487) Use Enter to select.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(4)</strong> The next window will be of Guided Storage Configuration. Select Use the entire disk option by using Tab and Space from the keyboard. (Screenshot- 488). Hit Enter and Confirm the action (Screenshot- 489).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(5)&nbsp;</strong>The next window will be of SSH setup installation. Select the Install OpenSSH server using space and press enter. This will install the OpenSSH server by default. (Screenshot- 490)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(6)&nbsp;</strong>The Installation of the kernel&nbsp;will begin (Screenshot- 491) and <strong>You encounter an Error here&nbsp;</strong>stating &#39;failed unmounting /cdrom&#39;. (Screenshot- 492)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To resolve this error get back to the Virtual Box dashboard and get into the settings of the Ubuntu Server VM being installed and remove the ISO file from Storage &gt; Control: IDE which we loaded previously.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(7) </strong>Open back the VM and press Enter and the Installation process will continue. (Screenshot- 493)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(8)</strong> Enter the Username and Password to Login into the Ubuntu Server (Screenshot- 494, 495)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Installation of Ubuntu Server&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Configuring Ubuntu server</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-05-19', '2021-05-20', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-05-20 07:38:03', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
