(191, 178, 42, '<p>PFSense is mostly used as&nbsp;a router and firewall software&nbsp;and is typically configured as a DHCP server, DNS server, WiFi access point, VPN server, all running on the same hardware device.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Router and Firewall</strong>: <em>(Screenshot- 40)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>pfsense can be configured as a router and firewall for a LAN network.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>pfsense can be bought into action by purchasing the Netgate&#39;s product which comes with preconfigured pfsense software in it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If this is not the case we can just download the pfsense in .iso format and can be installed in Virtual Box, as we did <em>(Screenshot- 42)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>And once configured we can access its interface through web browser using its IP Address for configuring firewalls. <em>(Screenshot- 41)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Types of firewalls we can configure</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Packet Filter Firewalls</li>\r\n	<li>Stateful Packet Inspection</li>\r\n	<li>Proxy Server Firewalls</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Attack prevention:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The types of attack prevention that make sense at the network edge include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Intrusion detection and prevention</li>\r\n	<li>Network traffic analysis</li>\r\n	<li>Deep packet inspection</li>\r\n	<li>Application blocking</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>VPN</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A Virtual Private Network (VPN) provides secure network connections to traverse a public network, like the Internet. VPNs encrypt your internet traffic and conceal your online identity in real-time, making it more difficult for third parties to track your online activity or steal your data. There are two basic kinds of VPNs: remote-access and site-to-site.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Supports the most popular technologies: IPsec.OpenVPN, L2TP, and PPTP</li>\r\n	<li>Supports remote-access and site-to-site use cases</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '<ul>\r\n	<li>overview of pfsense and its features</li>\r\n	<li>Installing pfsense in virtual box</li>\r\n	<li>creating a firewall in pfsense</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-11-05', '2021-11-06', 1, '5', 'Y', 0, '2021-11-05 19:20:55', '1970-01-01', '28', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
