(195, 182, 42, '<p><strong>Creating .MSI Package(also known as Windows Installer Package) with a single application to be installed:</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Steps:</strong><br />\r\n<strong>(1)</strong> Install the MSI Wrapper from exemsi.com <em>(Screenshot- 554)</em><br />\r\n<strong>(2)</strong> Load the exe file of an application for which the MSI package is to be created&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 555,556)</em><br />\r\n<strong>(3)</strong> Leave the &#39;Visibility in Apps &amp; features&#39; and &#39;Security and User context&#39; settings as default and click &#39;next&#39; <em>(Screenshot- 557,558)</em><br />\r\n<strong>(4)</strong> In the next window load the Application ID from the lookup module by selecting the MSI wrapper application from the list. <em>(Screenshot- 560)</em><br />\r\n<strong>(5)</strong> In the same window, Upgrade code section click on the Create New button. <em>(Screenshot- 561)</em><br />\r\n<strong>(6)</strong> Leave the &#39;Properties&#39;, Parameters, and Actions windows as default and click next. <em>(Screenshot- 562,563,564)</em><br />\r\n<strong>(7)</strong> The Next window displays the complete pre-information about the MSI package to be created (565). Click on the Build button at the bottom of the window.<br />\r\n<strong>(8)</strong> The MSI Package is created successfully. <em>(Screenshot- 566)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Get to the location which was defined to store the MSI Package and we can view the MSI file that has been generated. <em>(Screenshot- 567)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Creating .MSI Package with Multiple applications loaded in it:<br />\r\nSteps:</strong><br />\r\n<strong>(1)</strong> Install the EMCO MSI Package Builder from the Emco.com <em>(Screenshot- 573)</em><br />\r\n<strong>(2)</strong> Select &#39;Wrapping&#39; as Repackaging Method <em>(Screenshot- 573)</em><br />\r\n<strong>(3)</strong> Select the Application to be included in the MSI package(Applications are added one at a time) <em>(Screenshot- 574)</em><br />\r\n<strong>(4)</strong> Specify the Name for the project and click on &#39;Add package&#39; to add another application to be Included in the MSI package<em>(Screenshot- 575)</em><br />\r\n<strong>(5)</strong> Select the MSI path(where the MSI Package is to be stored post generation) and Specify a name for the MSI Package and In the Manufacturer section enter any name and click on &#39;Finish&#39;.<em>(Screenshot- 577)</em><br />\r\n<strong>(6)</strong> We can view the MSI Package being created <em>(Screenshot- 570)</em><br />\r\n<strong>(7)</strong> Get to the location which was defined to store the MSI Package and MSI Package is Ready for Deployment&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 572)</em></p>\r\n', '', '', '', '2021-05-29', '2021-05-29', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-05-29 11:11:49', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
