(197, 184, 42, '<p><strong>Router Sploit:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Routersploit</strong>&nbsp;is a tool for originally hacking routers. But with a recent update, they have included the option to hack cameras of certain models using exploits available on the internet. This has made Routersploit a Camerasploit too.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nBecause RouterSploit is a Python module, Python3 and Python PIP (for installing Python modules) must also be present on the computer:<br />\r\n<strong>sudo apt-get install python3-pip</strong> <em>(Screenshot- 604)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Installing Router Sploit tool for finding Vulnerabilities in CCTV:<br />\r\n<strong>git clone https://www.github.com/threat9/routersploit</strong> (<em>Screenshot- 604)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Installing Requirements for the Router Sploit:<br />\r\n<strong>cd routersploit&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\n<strong>python3 -m pip install -r requirements.txt </strong><em>(Screenshot- 604)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Starting RouterSploit:<br />\r\n<strong>python3 rsf.py </strong><em>(Screenshot- 605)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nUsing autopwn:&nbsp;This is a module which not only tests for vulnerabilities but will also attempt to exploit them automatically.<br />\r\n<strong>rsf&gt; search autopwn&nbsp;<br />\r\nrsf&gt; use scanners/autopwn </strong><em>(Screenshot- 605)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Setting a Target CCTV for Pentesting:<br />\r\n<strong>rsf (Autopwn) &gt; set target 192.168.0.13</strong> (IP Address)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now running the Exploit scanner:<br />\r\n<strong>rsf (Autopwn) &gt; run</strong> <em>(Screenshot- 606)</em><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nThe tool will run multiple exploits and check if the device is vulnerable. If the device is vulnerable, it lists out all the vulnerabilities found. <em>(Screenshot- 607)</em></p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Penetration testing of CCTV cameras using the tool RouterSploit</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-06-26', '2021-06-26', 1, '', 'Y', 0, '2021-06-26 15:39:19', '0000-00-00', '', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
