(281, 250, 42, '<p><strong>Steps</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>1</strong>) Open the Browser &gt; Options &gt; Preferences (Screenshot - 92)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>2</strong>) Search for &#39;Proxy&#39; Settings (Screenshot - 93)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>3</strong>) Change the Proxy Access to &#39;Manual&#39; and Enter the Localhost IP Address (127.0.0.1) and also enter the desired Port number (we are using 8019 port number here) and click on the ok button (Screenshot - 94)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>4</strong>) Now, Open the Burpsuite and navigate to the Proxy section. (Screenshot - 95)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>5</strong>) In the proxy section open the Options tab and click on the Add button from Proxy Listeners section (Screenshot - 96)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>6</strong>) In the popped window enter the port number which we have configured in the Browser settings and change the Address to Specific and enter the Localhost IP (Screenshot - 97)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And hence the Proxy is configured with Localhost on a specific port.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Certificates issue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Update</strong>: Downloaded the CA certificate&nbsp;and added it to the browser</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Steps:&nbsp;Importing certificates:<br />\r\nBurpsuite&gt; Proxy &gt; Options &gt; import/Export CA Certificate &gt; Export &gt; Certificate in DER Format &gt; Save with der extension<br />\r\nBrowser &gt; Preferences &gt; Privacy &amp; Security &gt; Certificates &gt; import saved certificate</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Configuring Proxy server in Local browser with specific port</li>\r\n	<li>Configuring Burp Proxy</li>\r\n	<li>Importing Certificates for Burp to run Properly with the browser after proxy configuration.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-11-16', '2021-11-18', 1, '5', 'Y', 0, '2021-11-22 08:55:37', '1970-01-01', '28', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
