(350, 318, 42, '<p><strong>Creating Contract: </strong>(with the Master and Child Contract Linkage)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(1)</strong> In the Lifecycle section of the Eracent tool open the &lsquo;Contracts &amp; Procurement&rsquo; from the list at the top-left corner of the window.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(2)</strong> From the Contracts sub-list click on the &lsquo;Add new Contract&rsquo; to get the complete form to create a Contract.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(3)</strong> In the &lsquo;Group IT&rsquo; a sub list is displayed. Select the Contract type you want to create i.e, Hardware or Software or Telco. (Here we are creating a Software contract)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(4)</strong> A new Contract form will be opened. On the left part of the form, Enter the Contract number, Vendor (Search using the company name), and the Start date of the Contract.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(5) </strong>To Link the Master Contract, Click on the Master Contract search option from the right part of the form and Search the Contract already present, using the Contract number <em>(Screenshot- 720)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(6)</strong> Fill in the contract details in the bottom-right part of the form such as Billing type,Category, Contract Owner, Contract Title, Pricing Mechanism, etc. <em>(Screenshot- 718)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(7)</strong> After filling the required fields, click on the &lsquo;Add New&rsquo; button at the bottom of the window. With this the Contract will be saved and can be viewed from the <a href=\"http://poc.digitowork.com/EnterpriseLM/LifecycleReportsMenu\">Lifecycle</a>&gt;<a href=\"http://poc.digitowork.com/EnterpriseLM/ContractsAndProcurementMenu\">Contracts &amp; Procurement</a>&gt;<a href=\"http://poc.digitowork.com/EnterpriseLM/ContractsAndProcurementMenu/ContractsAndProcurement_2/Contracts_1\">Contracts</a>&gt;<a href=\"http://poc.digitowork.com/EnterpriseLM/BrowseContracts.aspx?restore=y\">View/Edit Contracts</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>(Screenshot- 719)</em></p>\r\n', '', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Creating contract</li>\r\n	<li>Linking contract with Master contract</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-08-18', '2021-08-18', 1, '5', 'Y', 0, '2021-08-18 10:55:10', '2021-08-18', '28', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(351, 319, 42, '<p><strong>Creating Purchase Order (PO): </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(1)</strong> In the Lifecycle section of Eracent tool open the &lsquo;Contracts &amp; Procurement&rsquo; from the list at the top-left corner of the window.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(2)</strong> From the Purchase Orders sub-list click on the &lsquo;Add new Purchase Order&rsquo; to get complete form to create a PO.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(3)</strong> Define the Purchase Order Number as required, Purchase Order status, Asset Purchased- Search the company by name and add, Requested by- Search the employee by name and add, Submitted by- Search the employee by name and add, Add Purchase date, Ticket number as required.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(4)</strong> To link a Contract, click on the &lsquo;Contract number&rsquo; search box and search for the contract created previously using contract number and add the contract for the PO respectively.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(5)</strong> In the next section add the Sales Tax rate, VAT Tax rate, Local currency shipping cost, etc as per the requirement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(6)</strong> Add the Bill and Shipping details using the search box and assign the nae of the employee.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>(Screenshot- 721)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(7)</strong> In the next section, Add the Expected date for the order to be delivered, Payment Terms- Defines the days within which the supplier must be paid.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(8)</strong> Add the remaining details such as PO Delivery date, PO Start date, PO End date, Project code and Project name as required, Supplier ID, Ticket number, and Warranty period. <em>(Screenshot- 722)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(9)</strong> Finally, click on the &lsquo;Add New&rsquo; button to save the PO. A Confirmation message will be displayed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>(Screenshot- 723)</em></p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Creating Purchase Order.</li>\r\n	<li>Linking PO with Contract.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-08-18', '2021-08-19', 1, '5', 'Y', 0, '2021-08-19 09:46:13', '1970-01-01', '28', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
