(353, 321, 42, '<p><strong>Creating Hardware Asset followed by Catalog:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Creating Hardware Catalog, Steps:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>1</strong>)&nbsp;Go to the Lifecycle section and click on &#39;Catalog&#39; &gt; &#39;Hardware Catalog&#39;&nbsp; &gt; &#39;Add New Hardware Item&#39; in the menu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>2</strong>) Select the required item to be added for creating a catalog from the Hardware list. Here we are selecting hardware &gt; Computer &gt; Laptop and click on create new button at the bottom.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>3</strong>) A new catalog form will be displayed with the category preloaded with&nbsp;hardware &gt; Computer &gt; Laptop.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>4</strong>) Add the Catalog Item name for future reference to the catalog, Select the catalog status, Make and Model which defines the manufacturing company of the product, and the model which is being defined in the catalog. These fields are enough to create a catalog.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>5</strong>) We will fill more details in the catalog such as Part Number, Number of Physical Processors, Processor Type, Memory in MB i.e, RAM, Harddisk capacity in MB, Depreciation period, Support End Date, Unit Cost, and also&nbsp;any other field as required.&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 732)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>6</strong>) After filling in the required details, click on the &#39;Add New&#39; button at the bottom of the page. A confirmation message will be displayed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Catalog Created..!! <em>(Screenshot- 732, 733)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Creating Hardware Asset, Steps:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>1</strong>)&nbsp;Go to the Lifecycle section and from the Hardware&nbsp;sub-list click on &#39;Add new Hardware Asset&#39;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>2</strong>) A Catalog search window will be displayed here. The&nbsp;first requirement at this stage is to select the catalog item from which the asset is derived. Search the Catalog using the Catalog item name&nbsp;and click on add.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>3</strong>) An Asset form will be displayed with the preloaded details from the catalog. Here the Current status is the mandatory field to create an asset. Select the status from the dropdown menu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>4</strong>) Add the details such as, Location, Ownership status, Usage, Bar code, IP Address of the laptop, Number of cores, Machine name, Maintainance start and end date, Team responsible, and other fields as per the requirement.&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 735)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>5</strong>) After filling all the required details, click on the &#39;Add new&#39; button at the bottom of the page.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A confirmation message of the Asset been created will be displayed.&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 735, 736)</em></p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Creating Hardware Catalog</li>\r\n	<li>Creating a Hardware Asset linked with&nbsp;the Catalog created previously.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-08-19', '2021-08-20', 1, '5', 'Y', 0, '2021-08-21 05:39:49', '1970-01-01', '28', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(354, 322, 42, '<p><strong>Creating Hardware Catalog, Steps:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>1</strong>)&nbsp;Go to the Lifecycle section and click on &#39;Catalog&#39; &gt; &#39;Hardware Catalog&#39;&nbsp; &gt; &#39;Add New Hardware Item&#39; in the menu.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>2</strong>) Select the required item to be added for creating a catalog from the Hardware list. Here we are selecting hardware &gt; Computer &gt; Laptop and click on create new button at the bottom.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>3</strong>) A new catalog form will be displayed with the category preloaded with&nbsp;hardware &gt; Computer &gt; Laptop.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>4</strong>) Add the Catalog Item name for future reference to the catalog, Select the catalog status, Make and Model which defines the manufacturing company of the product, and the model which is being defined in the catalog. These fields are enough to create a catalog.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>5</strong>) We will fill more details in the catalog such as Part Number, Number of Physical Processors, Processor Type, Memory in MB i.e, RAM, Harddisk capacity in MB, Depreciation period, Support End Date, Unit Cost, and also&nbsp;any other field as required.&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 732)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>6</strong>) After filling in the required details, click on the &#39;Add New&#39; button at the bottom of the page. A confirmation message will be displayed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Catalog Created..!! <em>(Screenshot- 732, 733)</em></p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Creating Hardware Catalog. (Created a Catalog for a Laptop)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-08-19', '2021-08-19', 1, '5', 'Y', 0, '2021-08-21 05:41:53', '1970-01-01', '28', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
