(365, 333, 42, '<p><strong>Creating Employee, Steps:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>1</strong>)&nbsp;To create a new employee, go to the Lifecycle section and click &#39;People &amp; Organizations&#39;,&nbsp;and from the right side of the window in the Employees sublist click on&nbsp;&#39;Add New Employee&#39;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>2</strong>) A New form will be displayed for defining employee details to be created.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>3</strong>) Enter the fields - First name, Last name, Employee&nbsp;Address, Location, City, Zip code, Country, State, Mobile Number, Email, Start date, User status, User type, User status, Contract end date, and other fields if required.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>4</strong>) Add the Supervisor of the employee being created by searching by the person&#39;s name and click on add button.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>5</strong>) Since the required fields are filled click on the &#39;Add&nbsp;new&#39; button at the bottom of the window and the confirmation message will be displayed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>(Screenshot- 738, 739)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Updating Employee:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>1</strong>) To update the employee data present in the database, Go to the Lifecycle section and click on the &#39;People &amp;&nbsp;Organizations&#39; &gt; &#39;Employees&#39; &gt; &#39;View/Edit Employees&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>2</strong>) A search window will be displayed. We can perform the search using the keys such as&nbsp;First name, Last name,&nbsp;City, Country, State, Email, User type, User status.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>3</strong>) Enter any of the above-mentioned fields of the employee to be updated and click on the search button.&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 740)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>4</strong>) The search results are displayed below the search window. Select the required employee and the employee form will be displayed with all the details filled at the time of creation/last-update.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>5</strong>) Add/Delete the required fields from the employee data and click on &#39;Save and Close&#39; button at the bottom of the window.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>(Screenshot- 740)</em></p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Creating New employee data</li>\r\n	<li>Updating Details of the Employee</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-08-20', '2021-08-21', 1, '5', 'Y', 0, '2021-08-21 09:50:02', '1970-01-01', '28', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(366, 334, 42, '<p><strong>Adding Vendor:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(1) To add a new Vendor, go to the Lifecycle section and click &#39;People and Catalog&#39; and now in the &#39;Companies&#39; section click on &#39;Add new Company&#39;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(2) A new company form will be displayed, Here to create a new vendor the two fields, Company name and Vendor ID are needed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(3) Add the fields, Website, Company notes, Aliases, Default location, City, State, Country, Zipcode as required.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(4) In the Relationships section click on &#39;Add Relationship&#39; and map the required relationship titles from Unassigned to Assigned Relationships section accordingly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(5) Add the documents if any and click on &#39;Add new&#39; button at the bottom of the window. A Confirmation message will be displayed.<em> (Screenshot- 742,743)</em></p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Adding a New Vendor</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-08-24', '2021-08-25', 1, '5', 'Y', 0, '2021-08-25 07:42:46', '1970-01-01', '28', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(367, 335, 57, '<p>Created EPR and upload in POC to convert INR to USD.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>If any user saved currency in INR in PO Line Item, then&nbsp;it will convert into USD.</li>\r\n	<li>If the Local Currency is INR then he needs to maintain UDF Fields.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Steps Followed:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Prepare a UDF field on the PO Line item level</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. If the PO currency is other than USD then it should convert to USD</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. This USD value should be added to the total PO value</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Note:- If the user wants to see INR value he needs to maintain PO Item Level UDF Fields.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>UDF Fields:- <strong>PO Local Currency Unit Cost (In INR)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;PO Local Currency Total Cost (In INR)</strong></p>\r\n', '', '<p>Created EPR and upload in POC to convert INR to USD.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>If any user saved currency in INR in PO Line Item, then&nbsp;it will convert into USD.</li>\r\n	<li>If the Local Currency is INR then he needs to maintain UDF Fields.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Steps Followed:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Prepare a UDF field on the PO Line item level</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. If the PO currency is other than USD then it should convert to USD</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. This USD value should be added to the total PO value</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Note:- If the user wants to see INR value he needs to maintain PO Item Level UDF Fields.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>UDF Fields:- <strong>PO Local Currency Unit Cost (In INR)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;PO Local Currency Total Cost (In INR)</strong></p>\r\n', '', '2021-08-20', '2021-08-20', 1, '5', 'Y', 0, '2021-09-19 22:38:20', '2021-08-23', '28', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
