(377, 344, 42, '<p><strong>Loading Employee&nbsp;data through CSV file:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>1</strong>) To load the employee data using a CSV file, We need to Identify the fields needed for creating an employee, which can be noted down from the employee form while doing the manual entry&nbsp;of the employee.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>2</strong>) Now we need to create a CSV file with the appropriate data of employees. (<em>Please find the File I&#39;ve created- csv1.csv)/ Screenshot- 746)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>3</strong>) Here we added the fields- First Name, Last Name, Email, HR Identifier, Supervisor First Name, Supervisor Last Name, Supervisor HR Identifier 1. Save the file in your system using the extension (.csv)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>4</strong>) Now come to the &#39;Data Sharing&#39; section&nbsp;in the Eracent and click on &#39;Import data&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>5</strong>) Select the &#39;Text File&#39; option and click on the &#39;Import&#39; button.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>6</strong>) In the next window select &#39;MS Excel Comma Delimited file&#39; and click on the browse button and select the CSV file created previously. Now&nbsp;click on the next button leaving other fields as default.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>7</strong>) Now in the next window, Leave the 1st and 2nd sections as default. In the 3rd section i.e, &#39;Source fields to Import&#39; click on &#39;select all&#39; button.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>8</strong>) In the Single field mappings select the default table as &#39;Employees&#39; and click on &#39;Apply for all fields&#39; button.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>9</strong>) In the same window,&nbsp;Map the fields of the employee table accordingly from the category dropdown. <em>(Screenshot- 744)&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>9</strong>) Save the current settings if needed for future use by defining the Setting name at the top right corner of the page and click on save settings button.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>10</strong>) Click on the Next button and a Table will be displayed as processed with the CSV file uploaded previously. If the data in the table is appropriate click on the Next button.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>11</strong>) The data will be processed and a confirmation of the number of records entered will be displayed.&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 745)</em></p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Creating CSV files by Identifying appropriate fields.</li>\r\n	<li>Loading more than one Employee&#39;s data through CSV file.</li>\r\n	<li>Defining Supervisors: different supervisors for different employees in the same CSV file.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-08-24', '2021-08-25', 1, '5', 'Y', 0, '2021-08-25 14:43:32', '1970-01-01', '28', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N');
