(378, 345, 42, '<p><strong>Appending Asset Notes through Data Sharing:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(1)&nbsp;</strong>Open the Asset form&nbsp;which you want to update from the Lifecycle section and clicking on Assets &gt; View/Edit Assets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here we are using a software asset with Catalog item name &#39;Oracle Database&#39; <em>(Screenshot-757)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(2) </strong>Here the predefined asset notes are &#39;Hi, this is the first note..!!&#39;. Our requirement is to add other two&nbsp;lines of asset notes by appending the present note. So copy the present note that should be added with the other two lines of notes in the CSV file.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(3) </strong>Create a new CSV file in which we need to define a minimum of two fields i.e, The field we want to update (Asset notes) and one Primary key field (Serial number).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(4)</strong> In the Asset Notes column of the CSV file, paste the first note copied from the asset form and Enter the other two lines of notes which need to be appended (in&nbsp;multiple lines using ALT + Enter keys).&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot-758)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(5)</strong> Enter the Serial number of the asset beside the Asset notes column in the CSV file and save it with the .csv extension.&nbsp;&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot-758)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(6)</strong> Now Go to the Data sharing in the Lifecycle section and click on the Import data option from the list.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(7)</strong> Set the Text file format to &#39;MS Excel comma-delimited&nbsp;file&#39;, Upload the saved CSV file to import, and check the boxes - &#39;First row contains column names&#39;, &#39;Allow multi-line values&#39; and proceed to the next window.&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot-759)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(8)</strong> A new CSV import wizard will be opened, In the 1st section- Updates and Inserts behavior, move the &#39;Assets&#39; from &#39;Standard Tables&#39; section to &#39;Update only&#39; section. <em>(Screenshot- 761)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(9)</strong> In the 3rd section-&nbsp; Source fields to import,&nbsp;click on the &#39;Select all&#39; button to select all the columns from the CSV&nbsp; file.&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 761)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(10)</strong> In the 7th section- Single field mappings, Set the default table to &#39;Assets&#39; and click on Apply for&nbsp;all fields. And map the columns to respective field names from the dropdowns. <em>(Screenshot- 761)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(11)</strong> Leave the other fields as default and click on the Next button, the&nbsp;validated data will be displayed for final verification before being updated to the Eracent database check and click the Next button.<em>&nbsp;(Screenshot- 762)&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(12)</strong> A confirmation message of the data been&nbsp;updated will be displayed.&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 763)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>(13)</strong> Open the updated asset from the &#39;Assets&#39; section in another window and you can find the Asset Notes&nbsp;have been updated.&nbsp;<em>(Screenshot- 764)&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Updating particular field&#39;s data through Data Sharting using CSV files.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-08-25', '2021-08-27', 1, '5', 'Y', 0, '2021-08-27 08:43:54', '1970-01-01', '28', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
