(394, 361, 42, '<p><strong>Batch Update:&nbsp;</strong>A Batch update is a set of multiple update statements which are submitted to the database for processing as a batch. Sending multiple update statements together can be more efficient than sending each statement separately.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Importance:&nbsp;</strong>As a&nbsp;single entity contains a number of different fields of interrelated data, For updating these fields individually may not be possible in case of huge data updates.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To overcome these issues an update called Batch update has been introduced where multiple interrelated data fields can be updated by sending the updates in the&nbsp;form of Sets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These sets carry out different fields to be updated in a particular entity solving the time-consuming process of data updations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Batch Update for Single Asset in Eracent:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(1) Go to the Lifecycle section in the Eracent and click on Assets &gt;Asset Tasks (Batch Update).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(2) An empty asset fields form will be displayed with checkboxes aside with each fields which has to be marked for including the fields which are to be updated. (Screenshot- 793)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(3) Mark the required field checkboxes and enter&nbsp;data for the fields accordingly. (Screenshot- 794)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(4) Search for the Asset which is to be updated from the bottom of the page where we can search for the Assets using unique Asset fields (like Serial Number) and Mark the Asset checkbox to select it. (Screenshot- 795)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(5) Click on the &#39;Perform Batch Update&#39; button present right above the Querying area on the same page and you will get a confirmation message about the asset been updated. (Screenshot- 797)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Batch Update for Multiple Assets:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(1) Go to the Lifecycle section in the Eracent and click on Assets &gt;Asset Tasks (Batch Update).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(2) An empty asset fields form will be displayed with checkboxes aside with each fields which has to be marked for including the fields which are to be updated. (Screenshot- 793)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(3) Mark the required field checkboxes and enter&nbsp;data for the fields accordingly. (Screenshot- 794)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(4) Search for the Assets which are&nbsp;to be updated from the bottom of the page where we can search for the Assets using unique Asset fields&nbsp;and Mark the Asset checkboxes of the required Multiple Assets to be updated. (Screenshot- 799)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(5) Click on the &#39;Perform Batch Update&#39; button present right above the Querying area on the same page and you will get a confirmation message about the asset been updated. (Screenshot- 798)</p>\r\n', '', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Batch Updating for Single and Multiple Assets</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-09-03', '2021-09-04', 1, '5', 'Y', 0, '2021-09-06 09:49:35', '1970-01-01', '28', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(395, 362, 42, '<p>Burp is a commercial closed source tool (which can be extended) developed by a commercial company.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Burpsuite has to be configured to work as a proxy between your browser and the target server.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Burpsuite can be used as a Proxy Server, With a Proxy server, we can capture the browser requests before they reach the Server for which the request was made.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Proxy Tab in the Burpsuite is where we can configure Proxy Server and Turn on/off Intercept which is used to capture the browser requests.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the Proxy section, We can do much more like Configuring Proxy Listeners,&nbsp;specifying which client requests for Intercepting, specifying&nbsp;which Server responses to intercept, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Configuring Proxy:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Steps</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>1</strong>) Open the Browser &gt; Options &gt; Preferences&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>2</strong>) Search for &#39;Proxy&#39; Settings&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>3</strong>) Change the Proxy Access to &#39;Manual&#39; and Enter the Localhost IP Address (127.0.0.1) and also enter the desired Port number (we are using 8019 port number here) and click on the ok button&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>4</strong>) Now, Open the Burpsuite and navigate to the Proxy section.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>5</strong>) In the proxy section open the Options tab and click on the Add button from Proxy Listeners section</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>6</strong>) In the popped window enter the port number which we have configured in the Browser settings and change the Address to Specific and enter the Localhost IP&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And hence the Proxy is configured with Localhost on a specific port.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Intercepting Traffic:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>1</strong>) Turn the Intercept On in the Burpsuite&#39;s Proxy Section.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>2</strong>) Now Open the Browser which we have configured with the Proxy using the port number and search for any URL we want to request. (We are searching for youtube.com)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The&nbsp;Youtube URL has not got us results and the browser keeps loading</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(<strong>3</strong>) While the browser keeps loading, The Burp&#39;s Intercept window will be popped up showing that our request has not reached the Server but was Captured by the Proxy server.</p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Burpsuite functionalities and features</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2021-12-27', '2021-12-30', 1, '5', 'N', 0, '2021-12-30 07:07:16', '1970-01-01', '28', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(396, 363, 42, '<p>Some Burp Suite extensions like AuthMatrix, SAML Editor, etc require Jython. You can install Jython with the following instructions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1 Visit&nbsp; <a href=\"https://www.jython.org/download.html\">https://www.jython.org/download.html</a>&nbsp;and download the latest Jython standalone JAR file.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Screenshot- 173)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2 In Burp Suite, go to&nbsp;Extender&nbsp;-&gt;&nbsp;Options. Under the section&nbsp;Python Environment, click&nbsp;Select file.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Screenshot- 174)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3 In the popup window, navigate to the saved location and click on the downloaded Jython JAR file. Then click on&nbsp;<em>Open</em>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Screenshot- 175)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4 The&nbsp;Jython JAR file location will now be loaded in the&nbsp;<em>Python Environment</em>&nbsp;section.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Screenshot- 176)</p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<p>Installing Jython in Burp Suite</p>\r\n', '', '2022-01-03', '2022-01-04', 1, '5', 'Y', 0, '2022-01-06 06:51:08', '1970-01-01', '28', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
