(506, 471, 57, '<p><strong>Catalog Data Vs Asset Data: -</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>To reconcile the memory data from catalog to asset data: -</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For Catalog VS Asset Data Report: -</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Navigate this: - </strong>Lifecycle &gt; Reports &gt; Assets &gt; Asset Management &gt; Advanced User Defined Query for Assets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Steps: -</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Catalog should have <strong>Memory (MB), Hard Disk Capacity (MB) </strong>data in Catalog form.</li>\r\n	<li>Same Data will replicate during Asset Creation.</li>\r\n	<li>If someone has upgraded their assets like <strong>Memory (MB), Hard Disk Capacity (MB)</strong> with same catalog and asset form has updated by them.</li>\r\n	<li>Then we can easily distinct between from Catalog form <strong>Memory (MB), Hard Disk Capacity (MB) </strong>column data and Asset Form<strong> Memory (MB), Hard Disk Capacity (MB) </strong>data.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For Catalog VS Asset Data Report: -</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Navigate this: - </strong>Lifecycle &gt; Reports &gt; Assets &gt; Asset Management &gt; Advanced User Defined Query for Assets.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>In Advanced User Defined Query for Assets Query we can easily track all the catalog related asset data what are catalog data and what are asset data.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '', '', '2022-01-10', '2022-01-10', 1, '5', 'N', 0, '2022-01-10 05:43:13', '1970-01-01', '28', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
