(515, 475, 57, '<p>Yes, We can create multiple categories, sub-categories, and UDF Field in Asset form.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vivantio has the functionality to appear UDF field in Asset Form based on Category and Sub-Category.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>NA</p>\r\n', '', '', '2022-01-10', '2022-01-10', 1, '5', 'N', 0, '2022-01-10 06:08:07', '1970-01-01', '28', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(516, 478, 42, '<p>Right-click on the assembly&nbsp;code Search for &gt; All modules &gt; String references</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Screenshot- 187)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>An assembly code searching report will be displayed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We can see a line named &quot;This code is invalid&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Double click on it</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Screenshot- 188)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Edit the pre-mapping line of code where jne (Jump if not equal to) is displayed</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Change the line to je (Jump If euuals to)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Screenshot- 189)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Patch the code to save the code and alter the application&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Open the application and enter any string an we can see the Congratulations pop-up window is being displayed, Hence completed the challange</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Screenshot- 178)</p>\r\n', '', '', '', '2022-01-04', '2022-01-06', 1, '5', 'Y', 0, '2022-01-30 05:52:04', '1970-01-01', '28', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
(517, 479, 42, '<p>Go to the&nbsp;https://x64dbg.com/ and click on the Download button&nbsp;(Screenshot- 182)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The download file will be available at another site which will open automatically (https://sourceforge.net/projects/x64dbg/files/snapshots/) click on download latest version and a zip file will be downloaded</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Screenshot- 183)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unzip the file</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Open the X64&#39;s x32 application from the folder downloaded</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Click on the File dropdown from the top of the application and click on Open button</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Screenshot- 184)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>From the popup window, navigate to the file on which the RE has to be done and click on open button</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Screenshot- 185)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We can see that the file has been opened in the dashboard of the application</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Screenshot- 186)</p>\r\n', '<p>-</p>\r\n', '<p>Understanding the GUI and features of the tool and working of the tool</p>\r\n', '', '2022-01-04', '2022-01-05', 1, '5', 'Y', 0, '2022-01-30 05:52:04', '1970-01-01', '28', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
