(565, 512, 57, '<p><strong>&nbsp;IT Asset Risk Report:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Steps to get Asset Risk Report Based on Some Condition: -</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>If the IT Asset has these below 5 parameters, then the respective IT Asset has 100% score.&nbsp; The five parameters are:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1. IT Asset is discovered in last 14 days.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. The asset is active status and has a user assigned.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3. The asset has not completed its EOL.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4. The asset has a PO attached to it.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>5. If the Location is assigned.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Report Name: - IT Risk Report</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Navigate this path: </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lifecycle &gt; Reports &gt; Assets &gt; Asset Management &gt; Advanced User Defined Query for Assets</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Make a report as per above condition.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,', '<p>Discovery Report is not available in POC.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '', '2022-02-09', '2022-02-09', 1, '5', 'Y', 0, '2022-02-25 06:24:02', '1970-01-01', '28', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N');
