(578, 525, 42, '<p>Setting up a VPN Server in AWS and connecting clients to it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Report: please find the attached report: <strong>OpenVPN Server setup</strong>)</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>Updated Architecture for the requirement</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Report: <strong>VPN Architecture</strong>)</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>Update</strong>:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>we got a<strong> successful communication</strong> between the two clients connected to the VPN server hosted on AWS.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a Client1, I was hosting a webpage&nbsp;on my local Apache server, and</p>\r\n\r\n<p>as a Client2, Krishna sir was trying to access my hosted webpage. same as depicted in the VPN Architecture.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I&#39;ve attached the screenshots of the same sir.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The whole communication was done through a VPN tunnel, and we both as the clients we not exposed to the Internet.</li>\r\n	<li>The Public Ip address of the clients can be seen in the above screenshots, It was the Ip address of the VPN server.</li>\r\n	<li>Only when the clients are connected to the VPN, they are able to access the hosted website.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Setting up a VPN Server in AWS</li>\r\n	<li>Hosting private websites to the organization</li>\r\n	<li>VPN Connectivity (server and clients)</li>\r\n	<li>Possible communication apart from internet directly</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2022-02-09', '2022-02-16', 1, '5', 'N', 0, '2022-05-06 11:16:19', '1970-01-01', '54', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
