(597, 544, 42, '<p><strong>OpenVPN Access Server</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>This provides us with a web-based admin portal that makes VPN configuration and management easier.</li>\r\n	<li>We can configure users and their access.</li>\r\n	<li>As per our requirement, We can make the website only accessible through VPN.</li>\r\n	<li>As hosted in AWS, we can have the server running all the time.</li>\r\n	<li>Our server, where the website is hosted, can be set as one of the clients in the VPN network and only the users we grant can enter this network for further access</li>\r\n	<li>Multifactor authentication enabled, users&nbsp;have to enter their credentials before connecting to the VPN network.</li>\r\n	<li>Accommodates Windows, macOS, Linux (32-bit&nbsp;and 62-bit), Mobile OS (Android and iOS) environments.</li>\r\n	<li>We can select the package as per the&nbsp;requirement of concurrently connected devices. (Eg: If for the first month we have 5&nbsp;clients connected, and in the next month we want to revoke their access, it&#39;s possible to replace the old 5 clients with the new 5 ones)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>HOW?</strong> Once the VPN Server is hosted successfully in AWS, we can provide our clients wth the VPN software download link by providing credentials asked at the download page of OpenVPN website.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once the clients are connected to the VPN, they get special IP addresses allotted by the OpenVPN server and hence there&#39;s a communication channel enabled between the clients connected.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here the local company server (which is acting as one of the clients in the VPN connectivity) will host a website on its local port and not on the internet, hence using the details other clients (actual clients) in the network can only access the website hosted by the company server.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Attached is the Architecture of the describing the complete connectivity</strong></p>\r\n', '', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Got to learn about hosting private websites to the Organization</li>\r\n	<li>VPN Connectivity (Server and Clients)</li>\r\n	<li>Possible Communication apart from direct internet</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '2022-02-18', '2022-02-21', 1, '5', 'N', 0, '2022-05-06 11:12:07', '1970-01-01', '54', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'N'),
